        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-20T00:13:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s intended for humans debugging problems with the service, but I don\u0027t necessarily know who will want to consume it. Maybe some other service will use it to render dashboards, who knows.\n\nMy current intended use case is for a human who receives an alert saying prefix x is underprovisioned to use the List API to find the status of every member of that prefix. This gives a specific entity to debug in a more convenient way that scouring logs. For example if an instance is listed as created a long time ago but not yet connected it gives you the specific instance to SSH into to see what happened.",
      "parentUuid": "ce4b309b_1bd3db36",
      "revId": "5e16cb462b27cc3885de8a2565bb574858f419de",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
